  <spirit:description>The AMBA Accelerator Coherency Port Interface is defined in the AMBA spec as a subset of the ACE-Lite protocol. A number of ARM processors that have an Accelerator Coherency Port (ACP) use this subset. The ACP provides a port for local hardware accelerator components that benefit from an interface optimized for coherent cache line accesses.  For more information about ACP interface please refer to the AMBA AXI and ACE Protocol Specification (ARM IHI 0022E)</spirit:description>
